<small>
      Cook Time: <b>15</b> minutes
     Prep time: <b>5</b> minutes  </small>
<section id="ingredients">
      <h2> Ingredients: </h2>
          <ul>
      <li>favorite flavor of packaged ramen</li>
            <li><b>2</b> eggs</li>
      <li>small piece of beef/chicken</li>
      <li>garlic powder</li>
            <li>cheap vegetables of your choice <i>(carrot, bean sprouts, corn, green onion, spinach)</i></li>
            <li> soy sauce, seaweed, sesame seeds <i>(optional)</i></li>
    </ul>
    </section>
    <section id="#directions">

      <h2>Directions:</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>In deep pot, hard boil both eggs for around <b>10 minutes.</b></li>
      <li>Wash and cut all veggies into small slivers</li>
      <li>Cook meat properly and cut into thin pieces.</li>
      <li>Prepare ramen according to package instructions.</li>
      <li> Pour finished ramen into bowl.</li>
      <li> Peel and cut eggs in half, putting them on top of the ramen.</li>
      <li> Place other ingredience on top, allowing them to sit in the hot broth to fully cook and absorb the flavor.</li>
      </ol>
      </section>
